Author: ComputerGenie#2331
Content:
"didnt know how notaries work.. its like a secure node right?"
The shortest answer is that NNs record the block hash of a chain on a "more secure" chain and then record the hash value of that transaction on the original chain, creating a "checkpoint" from which all new blocks must come.
Over-simplified, but the basic premise
